Scaramella�s credibility as a soldier seems scarce, since he goes off to war with lance and buckler, but also to kiss a Jewess. We can only guess whether it was this character or his melody that proved fascinating to composers and improvisers, but what is certain is that Scaramella exists in multiple versions, from Josquin des Prez�s to Compere�s and to the adaptation for lute included in Hans Gerle�s Tabulatur auff die Laudten (1533).
